The reason why this is bad is the subject of the certificate presented (in this case - the issuer of the certificate is an internal PKI issuer for a sample customer in government vs. CyberArk being the issuer) that is imitating a valid issuer is NOT the CyberArk EPM-related issuer mentioned in the previous screenshot of a known good result where CyberArk signed the certificate via GlobalSign.
