SSL TLS Inspection considerations
We have proxy support built into the Windows and Linux Agent for direct proxy connections. For Mac OS, we would leverage the OS configuration.
https://docs.cyberark.com/Product-Doc/OnlineHelp/EPM/Latest/en/Content/Installation/Windows-InstallAgents.htm#Installationwithconfigurationdetails
Many proxies/web application firewalls such as zScaler, Websense, Fortigate, etc have the ability to do man-in-the-middle TLS inspection of web traffic. The EPM agent does not support this. So we need to exempt the EPM agent from SSL Inspection. For more information, please see this:
Example: https://help.zscaler.com/zia/certificate-pinning-and-ssl-inspection


